President Donald J. Trump issued a proclamation declaring September 3, 2017, as a National Day of Prayer for the Victims of Hurricane Harvey and for the country's response and recovery efforts. The proclamation acknowledges the devastation caused by Hurricane Harvey in Texas and Louisiana, including loss of life, injuries, and damage to homes and infrastructure. It expresses gratitude for those involved in rescue and relief efforts and urges Americans of all faiths to offer prayers for those affected by the hurricane. The proclamation also highlights the American spirit of service and resilience, emphasizing that no challenge is too great for the nation to overcome.